data.content:
**In .NET 11, sync I/O on the EF Core Cosmos DB provider is fully removed â€” no opt-in, no workaround.** Every synchronous call (`ToList()`, `First()`, `Count()`, `SaveChanges()`) will **always throw** at runtime.

In .NET 10 you could opt back in; in .NET 11 that escape hatch is gone.

**Fix â€” convert to async:**

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

This will ripple up â€” every caller of these methods must also become `async`/`await`. The Cosmos DB SDK is async-only, so there is no way to avoid this.
